description.text:
The BridgeUP Out-of-School Time program at the New York Public Library is proud to host the first-ever College Fair @ NYPL on September 29, 2017, from 10:00am to 2:00pm. The fair will take place at Bartos Forum located in the Stephen A. Schwarzman Library.
Colleges, universities, and community-based organizations will be present to share information and resources with students and families. Financial aid workshops will also take place during the college fair.
The College Fair will be free and open to all teens and their families. For school staff or community-based organizations bringing students to the college fair, please request a ticket for each student attending so that we can have an accurate count of potential attendees.
https://www.nypl.org/events/programs/2017/09/29/college-fair
NYPL BridgeUp is a free, year-round and interactive Out-of-School Time (“OST”) program provide by NYPL dedicated to helping students reach their potential.
